Part (a) Possible Scenarios and how memory is accessed:

Random Scenario- eviction of memory at random across 256 different addresses hard to guage actual efficieny because miss rate is random.

Multiple Localities- A center biased approach that discriminately eliminates the edges mainly while keeping the center.

Sequential - Goes from 0-256 in a cyclical manner (not very efficeint premptively)

Temporal Decay- Uses the swap in swap out system of rotating pages. 

Hot Spot- A high percentage as assigned a lower percentage of eviction is randomized this is ensure the most accessed are prevented from getting evicted.

